fscli
=====

Distributed filesystem client

synopsis
--------

fscli

description
-----------

This program can be used to access and maipulate files saved to distributed filesystem. When started, it connects to a file server described in its configuration file `conf/dfs_client.conf`.

Client shows a prompt and user can enter commands to it.

options
-------

Program takes no arguments, it can be configured using the configuration file in `conf/dfs_client.conf`

commands
--------
`ls` - list files in file system
`touch <file>` - create empty file
`edit <file>` - edit file contents
`cat <file>` - print file contents

see also
--------

fsdird, fsservd

authors
-------

Aaro Lehikoinen (aaro.lehikoinen@cs.helsinki.fi)

